  "governance_notes": "All children preserve Stage 1 semantics and Stage 2 interfaces. Resource fields derived from internal_leaf_accesses. ParseCommand has no data store accesses, so global_vars and data_operations are empty. PlaceOrder, CancelOrder, and TrackOrder have synchronized global_vars and data_operations. Capabilities follow the principle of least privilege. Constraints enforce business rules and atomicity. Acceptance criteria cover happy path and error cases.",
  "resource_audit": {
    "signature_preservation_detail": "All signatures unchanged from Stage 2: ParseCommand(input: dict) -> dict, PlaceOrder(order_data: dict) -> dict, CancelOrder(order_data: dict) -> dict, TrackOrder(order_data: dict) -> dict.",
